


Version: 0.7

Requirement
- apache rewrite mod extension
- mysql server

Intall

 - unzip
 - set apache document root to pcg/public/
 - create database sample
 - load the DOC/sample.sql mysql database
 - configure your database access in etc/config.ini
 - Load http://localhost/ and check for failed elements
 - when all elements are passed, delete or rename pcg/public/install.php
 
 
 Note: 
 This distib include Smarty. smarty need to write in smartyWorkDir/cache and smartyWorkDir/template_c.
 Generated classes are located in out folder. 
 Be sure that the httpd user can write in these 3 folders.
  
 The index.php located in out folder can be executed to test the classes with the sample database.
 
 Here, some example of apache configuration:
 
 On Windows
 <VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerAdmin webmaster@localhost
    DocumentRoot "C:\pcg\public"
    ServerName localhost
    ErrorLog "logs/pcg.log"
    CustomLog "logs/pcg-access.log" common
	<directory "C:\pcg\public">
		Options Indexes FollowSymLinks
		AllowOverride all
		Order Deny,Allow
		Allow from all
	</directory>
</VirtualHost>

 On Linux
<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerAdmin webmaster@localhost
    DocumentRoot "/home/pcg/public"
    ServerName localhost
    ErrorLog "logs/pcg.log"
    CustomLog "logs/pcg-access.log" common
	<directory "/home/pcg/public">
		Options Indexes FollowSymLinks
		AllowOverride all
		Order Deny,Allow
		Allow from all
	</directory>
</VirtualHost>